  thumbnail_sha256: str | None = Field(default=None, nullable=True)

### 3. src/models/tenant.py — VideoScene model
Add to the VideoScene class:
  rep_frame_sha256: str | None = Field(default=None, nullable=True)

### 4. src/repository/tenant.py — AssetRepository.update_proxy()
Find the update_proxy method. Add two optional parameters:
  proxy_sha256: str | None = None
  thumbnail_sha256: str | None = None
If either is provided (non-None), include it in the SQL update. If None, do not overwrite existing value (use COALESCE or conditional logic — prefer only setting it when non-None).

### 5. src/api/routers/jobs.py — proxy job-complete handler
In the `complete_job` endpoint, in the `if job.job_type == "proxy":` block:
After reading proxy_key, thumbnail_key, width, height from `data`, also read:
  proxy_sha256 = data.get("proxy_sha256")        # str | None
  thumbnail_sha256 = data.get("thumbnail_sha256")  # str | None
Pass both to asset_repo.update_proxy(). The existing call signature will be extended
with these two optional kwargs.

### 6. src/workers/proxy.py — ProxyWorker.process()
After generating proxy_bytes and thumb_bytes (before writing to storage):
  import hashlib
  proxy_sha256 = hashlib.sha256(proxy_bytes).hexdigest()
  thumbnail_sha256 = hashlib.sha256(thumb_bytes).hexdigest()
Add both to the returned dict:
  return {
      "proxy_key": proxy_key,
      "thumbnail_key": thumbnail_key,
      "width": width_orig,
      "height": height_orig,
      "proxy_sha256": proxy_sha256,
      "thumbnail_sha256": thumbnail_sha256,
  }

### 7. src/api/routers/video.py — chunk complete handler
Find where VideoScene rows are created in the chunk-complete endpoint. The scene dicts
submitted by the worker include proxy_key and thumbnail_key per scene.

In the VideoIndexWorker (src/workers/video_index_worker.py), rep frames are currently
written with `shutil.copy2(rep_path, dest)` — the bytes are never held in memory, so
there is no `rep_frame_bytes` variable to hash. Do NOT attempt to hash after the copy
using the dest path alone, as that would require a separate file read.

Instead, change the rep frame write to go through storage.write() which requires the
bytes in memory. Replace the shutil.copy2 call with:
  rep_frame_bytes = rep_path.read_bytes()
  rep_frame_sha256 = hashlib.sha256(rep_frame_bytes).hexdigest()
  self._storage.write(scene_rep_key, rep_frame_bytes)
  rep_path.unlink(missing_ok=True)

This mirrors what storage.write() does internally (atomic write via .tmp rename) and
gives you the bytes in memory to hash. The rep_path is a temp file, so reading it into
memory is safe — it is small (a single JPEG frame, typically < 1 MB).

Include rep_frame_sha256 in the scene dict submitted to the chunk-complete endpoint.

In the chunk-complete API handler, when creating VideoScene objects, read
`rep_frame_sha256` from the scene dict (optional, default None) and set it on the
VideoScene instance.

