## Summary Table

| Phase | What changes | Backward compatible |
|-------|-------------|---------------------|
| 1 | Schema (3 new nullable columns) + hash computed in ProxyWorker + stored via job-complete | Yes — columns nullable, new fields optional |
| 2 | New endpoint: `POST /v1/assets/{asset_id}/artifacts/{type}` | Yes — additive |
| 3 | New endpoint: `GET /v1/assets/{asset_id}/artifacts/{type}` | Yes — additive |
| 4 | New endpoint: `POST /v1/assets/state-check` | Yes — additive |
| 5 | New endpoint: `POST /v1/assets/{asset_id}/vision` | Yes — additive; job-complete unchanged |

After all five phases, a remote thick client can:
1. Upload proxies via Phase 2
2. Download proxies for local AI inference via Phase 3
3. Verify its cache before inference via Phase 4
4. Submit AI results with integrity checking via Phase 5

The existing single-host deployment is unchanged throughout.
